# Cronis Project Rules

You are contributing to **Cronis**, a premium client-side Fabric HUD framework for modern Hypixel SkyBlock.

## Project Goals

Always prioritize:

- Maintainability
- Readability
- Performance
- Consistency

Never sacrifice long-term quality for short-term speed.

## Scope

Only implement the requested task.

Do not implement additional features unless explicitly requested.

Do not modify unrelated files.

If requirements are unclear, ask questions before making assumptions.

## Architecture

Respect the existing project architecture.

Reuse existing systems instead of creating duplicate ones.

Keep the codebase modular and easy to extend.

## Performance

Performance is a feature.

Avoid unnecessary allocations.

Avoid unnecessary rendering work.

Never introduce code that could noticeably impact FPS without good reason.

## Hypixel Safety

Cronis must always remain fully compliant with Hypixel rules.

Never implement:

- Macros
- Automation
- Packet manipulation
- Auto clicking
- AFK systems
- Any feature that provides unfair gameplay advantages

If a requested feature may violate Hypixel rules, explain why instead of implementing it.

## Documentation

When adding new systems or public APIs, update documentation when appropriate.